Penelope Wolverines
August 6 at 3:14 PM ·

Virtual Meet the Teacher
August 11, 2020 @ Noon
Facebook Live

We hope that you'll be able to tune in to Facebook Live as Mrs. Hueske and Mr. Timmons lead everyone through the buildings to see the excited Faculty and Staff before the first day of school! We hope to capture the fun of getting to see your teacher and classroom, while limiting campus exposure from visitors.

The video will be up for families to watch if you can't join us at noon. Hope to see you all soon!

*** Following our Virtual Meet the Teacher, Mrs. Hueske and Mr. Timmons would like to show parents a few of the new routines and things for the 2020-2021 school year. ***

Items we plan to cover:
- Morning dropoff / Screening process
- signout@penelopeisd.org
- Parent Parking Spots
- WiFi expansion

David Z. Timmons
Superintendent

shared_text:
Penelope Wolverines
July 7 at 4:33 PM ·

Today, TEA released guidelines for returning to on campus instruction for the Fall. While we have been discussing what reopening would look like since April, this document gives us what will be required of us to welcome students back into our buildings.

In the coming weeks, we will be releasing our local plan for how our Wolverines will come back to learn. There are a few things I’m comfortable saying today:

1. Things will be different. TEA’s requirements are going to modify school operations as we had been accustomed to.
2. Penelope is going to follow all required steps and potentially some voluntary measures to ensure students, staff, and visitors will remain safe.
3. We are ALL going to have to work together to make this year successful. Extra things are going to be required of all of us and in the process, these measures may inconvenience or frustrate us at times.

As always, thank you for your support and understanding. Together we are going to make it a great year to be a Wolverine!

David Z. Timmons
Superintendent

Penelope Bso is with BJ Kucera and 5 others.
June 24 at 1:21 PM ·

Our peewee participants, volunteers, board members and everyone's safety is of our upmost importance in considering the current situation with the coronovirus this up coming football season.
So after a thorough review of UIL and CDC rules and recommendations the decision has been made not to move forward with peewee football this year.
If you have any questions please feel free to email us at bso@penelopeisd.org.

Thank you for your understanding.

Penelope Wolverines
May 19 at 2:23 PM ·

We are excited to announce the Honor Graduates for the Penelope High School Class of 2020.

Our VALEDICTORIAN is Jesus Silva. Jesus has a 4-year academic average of 95.6153 and a weighted average of 103.7076.

The SALUTATORIAN is Raul Cartagena. Raul has a 4-year academic average of 94.6800 and a weighted average of 102.8960.

Other honor graduates and their weighted averages are:
Maria Gonzalez - 99.3615
Nikki Beshears - 98.2300
Ben Griffin - 97.5560
Kearstyn Sexton - 96.1846
Baylee Bustillos - 94.2550
Courtney Westmoreland - 92.8750
Brenner Martin - 91.3000
Deven Lednicky - 90.7843

Congratulations to these listed and all of our Wolverine Graduates!

The federal census helps us all by creating accurate numbers that assist the federal government when establishing funding amounts or awarding grants.

We appreciate your patience and understanding as we work together while our Wolverines continue to Learn Away from School.

post_text:
En los últimos días recibimos las actualizaciones de parte del CDC y del Departamento de Servicios de Salud de Texas en cuanto a COVID-19. También estamos en contacto con los directores de los distritos de nuestro área. Entre todo medimos la salud y seguridad de nuestros estudiantes con las necesidades de los padres y la comunidad.
Las recomendaciones de hoy de parte del presidente Trump y el CDC es de reunir en grupos de menos de 10 personas. Según esta información, creo que la única opción que tenemos es extender las vacaciones de Spring break otra semana.

Favor de entender que no es una decisión que hacemos levemente.

Le notificaremos por llamadas, por Facebook, y por nuestro sitio del internet cuando haya nuevos desarrollos. Gracias por su paciencia y acuerdo mientras naviguemos está situación.

Sinceramente,

David Z.Timmons
Superintendent
Penelope ISD

shared_text:
Penelope Wolverines
March 16 at 8:14 PM ·

The past few days I have been monitoring guidance from the CDC and the COVID-19 reported cases from the Texas Department of State Health Services. I have also been monitoring the actions of our neighboring school districts. This entire time I have been weighing the health and safety of Penelope students with the needs of our parents and our community.

The new guidance today from President Trump and the CDC is for all Americans to limit groups to less than 10 people. Given this new information, I feel that in the best interest of keeping our Wolverines healthy, I have no choice than to close Penelope ISD for an additional week following Spring Break.

Please know that I do not take this decision or this responsibility lightly.

I will continue to update you through the all call system, on Facebook, and on our school website when there are new developments. Thank you for your patience and understanding as we navigate through this situation.

Sincerely,

David Z.Timmons
Superintendent
Penelope ISD

Congratulations to Kylia Redden who will serve as a District FFA Officer next school year.

Congratulations to our OAP for advancing to the B-District competition.

On Monday, Junior High Track will be running at St. Mary’s in West.

On Wednesday, Juniors and Seniors will have the opportunity to attend the Career Fair at Hill College. Please turn permission slips in by Tuesday to the HS Office.

Thursday, HS Track will be running at the Coolidge Track Meet.

On Friday, classes will dismiss at 1:00 o’clock for the start of Spring Break.

And A few other dates for your calendar…
Spring Break will run from March 16th through the 20th.
The Cajun Dinner will be March 21st. For tickets or more information, contact Mrs. Christian or an FFA Member.
Penelope OAP will be performing Of Mice and Men at the Bi-District Competition at Panola College in Carthage, Texas on March 24th. Performances start at 11:00 AM and Penelope will be the final performance.

post_text:
Wolverine Parents are invited to meet with teachers for a quick update on their child’s progress. Teachers will be ready for parents starting after the early dismissal at 1:00 PM and ending at 4:00 PM on February 8th.

These updates usually will not take more than 5 to 10 minutes to let you know your child’s strengths and also some things you can work on at home with them. This is a “come and go” styled event.

Contact your Wolverine’s teacher if you’d like to meet that day to schedule a time. If you cannot make it, you can also call and speak with their teacher. ***These meetings are not mandatory, but we want parents to have an opportunity for information.***

Educating our Wolverines is a team effort between parents and teachers. Thank you for your support and make today a great day to be a Wolverine!

post_text:
We are also hosting an “Essentials Shower” for Mrs. Harlin. As most of you know, the day before Thanksgiving Mrs. Harlin and her family lost virtually EVERYTHING (and I mean everything) in a house fire. Mrs. Harlin has dedicated (and I MEAN dedicated) so much of her life to the kids and community of Penelope. If a kid needed her, she was (is) here. If a program needed a sponsor, it was (is) her. If a teacher needed a shoulder, they could (and can) lean on her. It’s time to return that same love and devotion to her in her time of need.

We will hold the shower

after school lets out on
December 8th in the high school library.

Parents and community members are welcome and encouraged to help us put her family back on their feet. Appropriate gifts could be virtually anything the family could use. Cash and gifts cards are great, too. When trying to decide what or how much to give, walk through your house and picture every single thing in it suddenly gone. What would you miss? What would you want replaced? What would be most important?

post_text: From Tammy Christian: I wanted to share the results of yesterday’s contest in Cleburne; the kids really did well. We had 14 students who participated; Rachel Esquivel, Grace Kasberg, Amber Westmoreland, Amanda Christian, Amberly Jennings, Alex Eddy, Madison Quiram, Austin Todd, Logan Miller, Emily Labella, Abby Pineda, Shane Kelley, Cory Nave and Justin Esquivel. Jr. Chapter Conducting was 3rd, Jr. Quiz was 3rd, Radio was 4th, Sr. Quiz was 6th , Sr. Creed was 6th, Job Interview was 9th, and Jr. Creed 13th. Our 3rd places were one spot out of advancing to area. This is above and ahead of our showing last year; we entered more teams and had more success and I believe we worked harder this year. I am really proud of the kids; gradually we are making progress and I hope they are starting to believe in themselves a bit. Unlike UIL we compete against more schools much larger than us; Burleson, Alvarado, Glen Rose, Granbury just to name a few. Please congratulate these kids and thanks to all of you for you do.
